sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as odh-dashboard
    participant KServeCtrl as KServe Controller
    participant Runtime as vLLM / TGIS / OVMS
    participant ODHModel as odh-model-controller
    participant KubeAuth as kube-auth-proxy
    participant Authorino as Kuadrant / Authorino
    participant S3 as S3 Storage
    participant Client as External Client

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 1: Model Deployment (KServe InferenceService)

    User->>Dashboard: Create InferenceService via UI
    Note over Dashboard: 3-layer auth:<br/>Gateway → kube-rbac-proxy → BFF
    Dashboard->>KServeCtrl: InferenceService CR created
    KServeCtrl->>KServeCtrl: Reconcile — select runtime,<br/>create Knative Revision or Deployment,<br/>configure storage initializer
    KServeCtrl->>Runtime: Create predictor pod
    Runtime->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>(HTTPS/443, AWS IAM)
    Note over Runtime: Load model weights,<br/>start inference server
    Runtime-->>KServeCtrl: Pod ready
    KServeCtrl-->>ODHModel: InferenceService status updated
    ODHModel->>ODHModel: Create HTTPRoute for<br/>Gateway API ingress
    ODHModel->>Authorino: Create AuthPolicy for<br/>Kuadrant enforcement

    Note over Client,Runtime: Production Inference Flow
    Client->>KubeAuth: POST /v1/models/my-model:predict<br/>(HTTPS/443, TLS 1.3)
    KubeAuth->>Authorino: Validate API key / OIDC token
    Authorino-->>KubeAuth: Authorized
    KubeAuth->>Runtime: Forward to runtime pod<br/>(Istio mTLS)
    Runtime->>Runtime: Run inference
    Runtime-->>KubeAuth: Prediction result (mTLS)
    KubeAuth-->>Client: JSON response (HTTPS)

    User->>Dashboard: View model status
    Dashboard->>KServeCtrl: Query InferenceService status<br/>(K8s API, SA + user token)
    Dashboard-->>User: Model health, replicas, metrics

%% ---

    participant Notebook as Jupyter Notebook
    participant DSPO as DSPO API Server
    participant Argo as Argo Workflows
    participant MLMD as ML Metadata
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry

    Note over User,ModelReg: Workflow 2: Pipeline Execution (Data Science Pipelines)

    User->>Dashboard: Submit pipeline via UI
    Dashboard->>DSPO: Pipeline definition<br/>(HTTP, service-ca TLS)
    Note over DSPO: Validate pipeline,<br/>store in MariaDB

    DSPO->>Argo: Create Argo Workflow CR
    Argo->>Argo: Execute pipeline DAG —<br/>launch task pods in user namespace
    Note over Argo: Task pods use<br/>pipeline runtime images

    Argo->>S3: Store pipeline artifacts<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    Argo->>MLMD: Log execution metadata,<br/>artifact lineage (gRPC/8080)

    MLMD->>ModelReg: Register trained model<br/>(gRPC/9090, version tracking)
    ModelReg->>S3: Store artifact reference

    Note over ModelReg,KServeCtrl: Model ready for deployment
    ModelReg-->>KServeCtrl: Model metadata available<br/>for InferenceService creation

    User->>Dashboard: View pipeline results
    Dashboard->>DSPO: Query run status
    Dashboard->>ModelReg: Query registered models
    Dashboard-->>User: Pipeline status,<br/>model artifacts, lineage

%% ---

    participant SDK as CodeFlare SDK
    participant Kueue as Kueue
    participant KubeRay as KubeRay Operator
    participant CodeFlare as CodeFlare Operator
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Pod
    participant RayWorker as Ray Workers

    Note over User,RayWorker: Workflow 3: Distributed Training (CodeFlare + KubeRay)

    User->>Notebook: Write training script
    Notebook->>SDK: Submit RayJob via<br/>CodeFlare SDK

    SDK->>Kueue: Create Workload CR<br/>for quota admission
    Kueue->>Kueue: Evaluate ClusterQueue quotas,<br/>fair-sharing across workloads
    Note over Kueue: Admit when<br/>resources available

    Kueue->>KubeRay: RayCluster CR admitted
    KubeRay->>RayHead: Create head pod
    KubeRay->>RayWorker: Create worker pods

    CodeFlare->>RayHead: Watch RayCluster,<br/>create NetworkPolicies
    CodeFlare->>RayHead: Configure Gateway API<br/>HTTPRoute for dashboard
    Note over CodeFlare: Inject oauth-proxy sidecar<br/>via mutating webhook
    Note over RayHead: Init containers generate<br/>per-cluster mTLS certs

    RayHead->>RayWorker: Distribute training<br/>(mTLS encrypted)
    RayWorker->>S3: Load training data<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    RayWorker->>RayHead: Report metrics
    RayHead-->>Kueue: Workload completed

    User->>Dashboard: View Ray dashboard
    Note over Dashboard: Gateway → kube-auth-proxy<br/>→ oauth-proxy → Ray UI

%% ---

    participant AppClient as Client Application
    participant AIGW as AI Gateway (BBR)
    participant EPP as llm-d Scheduler (EPP)
    participant vLLM as vLLM Pod
    participant Orchestrator as FMS Guardrails<br/>Orchestrator
    participant Detectors as Guardrails Detectors<br/>(Regex, HF, LLM Judge)

    Note over AppClient,Detectors: Workflow 4: LLM Inference with Guardrails

    AppClient->>AIGW: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>(HTTPS/443, TLS 1.3)

    AIGW->>AIGW: BBR plugin pipeline:<br/>1. Resolve model provider<br/>2. Translate API format<br/>3. Inject API keys<br/>4. NeMo guardrails pre-check

    AIGW->>EPP: ext-proc gRPC —<br/>routing metadata

    EPP->>EPP: Score vLLM pods:<br/>- Prefix cache hit rate<br/>- Queue depth<br/>- KV cache utilization<br/>- LoRA affinity

    EPP->>vLLM: Route to optimal pod<br/>(disaggregated P/D)
    Note over vLLM: Prefill or decode phase<br/>NIXL V2 KV transfer<br/>between P and D pods

    vLLM->>Orchestrator: Stream tokens via SSE

    Orchestrator->>Orchestrator: Chunk streaming response
    Orchestrator->>Detectors: Fan out to detectors<br/>in parallel (HTTP/8080)
    Note over Detectors: Regex patterns,<br/>HuggingFace models,<br/>LLM Judge evaluation
    Detectors-->>Orchestrator: Safety annotations

    Orchestrator->>Orchestrator: Aggregate with<br/>ordering guarantees<br/>(DashMap, actor batcher)

    Orchestrator-->>AppClient: Annotated response<br/>(streamed, HTTPS)

%% ---

    participant EvalUser as Platform Engineer
    participant TrustyAIOp as TrustyAI Operator<br/>(LMES Controller)
    participant LMEval as lm-evaluation-harness<br/>Pod
    participant EvalHub as Eval Hub
    participant MLflow as MLflow

    Note over EvalUser,MLflow: Workflow 5: Model Evaluation and Safety

    EvalUser->>Dashboard: Create LMEvalJob CR<br/>(model, tasks, parameters)
    Dashboard->>TrustyAIOp: LMEvalJob CR created

    TrustyAIOp->>Kueue: Create Workload for<br/>quota admission
    Kueue-->>TrustyAIOp: Admitted

    TrustyAIOp->>LMEval: Launch evaluation pod<br/>with driver init container
    Note over TrustyAIOp: Direct pod management<br/>(not Jobs — custom lifecycle)

    LMEval->>Runtime: Run evaluation tasks<br/>against model endpoint
    Note over LMEval: Accuracy, perplexity,<br/>safety scores

    LMEval->>EvalHub: Report evaluation results
    EvalHub->>MLflow: Store in MLflow for<br/>experiment tracking<br/>(per-namespace, SeaweedFS)

    EvalUser->>Dashboard: View evaluation results
    Dashboard->>MLflow: Query experiment data
    Dashboard-->>EvalUser: Evaluation dashboard,<br/>safety scores, comparison
